===海伍德案===
{{See also|海伍德死亡案}}
2011年11月14日，英国公民[[尼尔·海伍德|尼尔·海伍德]]（官方通报中称其“尼爾·伍德”）被发现死于重庆南山丽景度假酒店客房。当时地方当局宣布其死因为[[酒精中毒|饮酒过量]]，但他的家人表示尼尔并不嗜酒。正式死因并未仔细勘验，直至几个月后尼尔·海伍德确定为死于他杀，薄熙来牵涉其中<ref name="au1"/>。

尼尔·海伍德是与中共政治家有关联的西方企业中介人<ref name="au1">{{cite news|url=http://www.theaustralian.com.au/news/world/british-fixers-murky-death-linked-to-fallen-leaders-wife/story-fnb64oi6-1226315844589|title=British fixer Neil Heywood's murky death linked to fallen leader Bo Xilai's wife|date=2012-04-02|author=Michael Sheridan|work=The Australian|accessdate=2012-04-10|archive-date=2012-04-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120410141853/http://www.theaustralian.com.au/news/world/british-fixers-murky-death-linked-to-fallen-leaders-wife/story-fnb64oi6-1226315844589|dead-url=no}}</ref>。他是薄家的长期助理，据称他跟薄熙来的妻子[[谷開來|谷开来]]有过亲密关系，并帮助夫妻俩的儿子[[薄瓜瓜|薄瓜瓜]]取得英国[[哈罗公学|哈罗公学]]的学位<ref name=wp-20120411>{{cite news |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2012/04/12/world/asia/bo-xilai-scandal-and-the-mysterious-neil-heywood.html |title=Briton's Wanderings Led Him to Heart of a Chinese Scandal |author=Sharon Lafraniere, John F. Burns |newspaper=The Washington Post |date=2012-04-11 |accessdate=2012-04-13 |archive-date=2012-04-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120414004856/http://www.nytimes.com/2012/04/12/world/asia/bo-xilai-scandal-and-the-mysterious-neil-heywood.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。海伍德还涉嫌充当薄家的中间人，协助他们将大笔资金秘密转移到海外<ref name=Telegraph05-06-2012>{{Cite news|title=Neil Heywood murder: Bo's wife, a French businessman and the £40 million property empire|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/asia/china/9248287/Neil-Heywood-murder-Bos-wife-a-French-businessman-and-the-40-million-property-empire.html|date=2012-05-06|accessdate=2020-07-19|issn=0307-1235|language=en-GB|first=Jason|last=Lewis|archive-date=2020-07-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200719142618/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/asia/china/9248287/Neil-Heywood-murder-Bos-wife-a-French-businessman-and-the-40-million-property-empire.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

2011年10月，据报道尼尔·海伍德与薄妻谷开来有商务纠纷，尼尔要求为他的服务提供更高的佣金<ref>Michael Forsythe [http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-22/bo-xilai-clan-links-included-citigroup-hiring-of-his-elder-son.html "Bo Xilai Clan Links Included Citigroup Hiring of Elder Son"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-22/bo-xilai-clan-links-included-citigroup-hiring-of-his-elder-son.html |date=20150110112340 }}, Bloomberg, 23 April 2012</ref><ref name="tuk-expose">{{Cite news|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/asia/china/9206308/Neil-Heywood-killed-because-he-threatened-to-expose-Gu-Kailais-money-trail.html|title=Neil Heywood killed 'because he threatened to expose Gu Kailai's money trail'.|work=The Daily Telegraph|date=2012-04-16|accessdate=2012-04-17|archive-date=2012-04-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120417123013/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/asia/china/9206308/Neil-Heywood-killed-because-he-threatened-to-expose-Gu-Kailais-money-trail.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>，否则公开薄家的业务往来和预计总额超过1.36亿美元的海外资产。海伍德当时据称被谷开来及其助手毒杀<ref>Damien McElroy and Malcolm Moore, [http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/asia/china/9224598/Bo-Xilais-wife-was-in-the-room-when-Neil-Heywood-was-poisoned.html Bo Xilai's wife 'was in the room when Neil Heywood was poisoned'] {{Wayback|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/asia/china/9224598/Bo-Xilais-wife-was-in-the-room-when-Neil-Heywood-was-poisoned.html |date=20120424223831 }}, ''The Daily Telegraph'', 24 April 2012.</ref>。

===被指發起窃听行动===
薄熙來被指发起了一场大型的电子监控行动，以协助打黑除恶专项行动，重庆市警察局长[[王立军|王立军]]担任这项国家资助项目的设计师，该项目被官媒形容为“覆盖电信互联网的综合配套窃听系统”<ref name=Eavesdrop/>。系统涉及窃听和互联网通信监控，其设计获得网络安全专家、[[防火长城|防火长城]]建设关键人物[[方滨兴|方滨兴]]的帮助<ref name=Eavesdrop>{{Cite news|title=Ousted Chinese Leader Is Said to Have Spied on Other Top Officials|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2012/04/26/world/asia/bo-xilai-said-to-have-spied-on-top-china-officials.html|newspaper=The New York Times|date=2012-04-25|accessdate=2020-07-19|issn=0362-4331|language=en-US|first=Jonathan|last=Ansfield|first2=Ian|last2=Johnson|archive-date=2020-09-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200902152304/https://www.nytimes.com/2012/04/26/world/asia/bo-xilai-said-to-have-spied-on-top-china-officials.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

据《[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]》报道，窃听行动不仅针对当地罪犯，还涉及包括時任中共中央总书记[[胡锦涛|胡锦涛]]在内[[党和国家领导人|党和国家领导人]]之间的通信<ref>{{Cite news|title=Bo Xilai 'spied on China leader'|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-china-17850570|newspaper=BBC News|date=2012-04-26|accessdate=2020-07-19|language=en-GB|archive-date=2020-08-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200828235142/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-china-17850570|dead-url=no}}</ref>。消息人士表示薄熙来企图监控所有到访过重庆的中央领导人，以便更好了解他们对自己的看法。2011年8月，胡锦涛与纪委官员[[马馼|马馼]]之间的电话通话被薄窃听。窃听透露的解释引来了中纪委的严格审查。据称该行动于2012年随着薄的下台而结束<ref name=Eavesdrop/>。

===蚁力神事件===
薄熙来在担任[[辽宁行政长官列表|辽宁省省长]]期间，与[[蚁力神|蚁力神]]董事长[[王奉友|王奉友]]等关系良好，曾多次视察蚁力神公司。中国商务部于2006年8月，部长薄熙來任内，颁给蚁力神[[直销|直销]]执照，被批准于辽宁省内14个市行政区域从事直销活动。由于之前有疑似添加西药的问题，且蚁力神从未有过直销经验，此举令直销业界感到惊讶<ref>{{cite news|author1=马晓华|title=蚁力神获直销牌照听取业内“惊”声一片|url=http://health.sohu.com/20060807/n244654759.shtml|accessdate=2015-08-11|work=搜狐网转自《第一财经日报》|agency=搜狐网|date=2006年8月7日|archive-date=2016-03-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305024249/http://health.sohu.com/20060807/n244654759.shtml|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

<ref name="Gutmann2012">{{cite journal |url = http://www.worldaffairsjournal.org/article/bitter-harvest-china%E2%80%99s-%E2%80%98organ-donation%E2%80%99-nightmare |title = Bitter Harvest: China's 'Organ Donation' Nightmare（苦痛的摘取：中国器官“捐献”的梦魇） |author = Ethan Gutmann |journal = ''Word Affairs''(全球事务) | year=2012 |issue = JULY/AUGUST（7/8月號） |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150323020421/http://www.worldaffairsjournal.org/article/bitter-harvest-china%E2%80%99s-%E2%80%98organ-donation%E2%80%99-nightmare |archivedate=2015-03-23 |dead-url=yes}}</ref>。且中共中央對此早有掌握<ref name=NYPOST2014Ethan>{{cite news |title=China’s long history of harvesting organs from living political foes（中共長期從政治異議人士摘取器官的歷史）|url = http://nypost.com/2014/08/09/chinas-long-history-of-harvesting-organs-from-living-political-prisoners/|date=2014-08-09 |last=Getlen|first=Larry|work=New York Post|language=en-US|archive-date=2014-08-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140811212811/http://nypost.com/2014/08/09/chinas-long-history-of-harvesting-organs-from-living-political-prisoners/|dead-url=no}}</ref>，因此在[[王立军事件|王立軍事件]]爆发后，當局迅速查封了[[大连市|大连市]]的人体标本厂<ref name="BOApple">{{cite news |url = http://www.epochtimes.com/b5/12/10/5/n3698537.htm |title = 香港蘋果日報：薄谷夫婦涉活摘法轮功器官撈巨資 |work=（[[大紀元時報|大紀元]]引述）香港[[蘋果日報_(香港)|蘋果日報]] | date=2012-10-04|archive-date=2015-09-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924032659/http://www.epochtimes.com/b5/12/10/5/n3698537.htm |dead-url=no}}</ref>。奧地利國家新聞社（APA）報導，薄熙來与掌管公安武警系统的中央政法委[[周永康|周永康]]主導了強摘囚犯器官系統與利益链<ref name="薄熙來參與器官交易">{{cite news |url = http://derstandard.at/1343745000326/China-Experte-Gestuerzter-KP-Poltiker-Bo-Xilai-in-Organhandel-verwickelt |title=China-Experte: Gestürzter KP-Politiker Bo Xilai in Organhandel verwickelt(中國專家：垮台的薄熙來參與器官交易) |work=Der Standard奧地利《標準報》、國家新聞社APA | date=2012-08-16 |author=Ethan Gutmann |quote=[http://www.epochtimes.com/gb/12/8/24/n3666765.htm?p=all 中文編譯|archive-date=2015-07-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150701082